<h2>Get Involved!</h2>
<pre>There are many ways to get involved in FIRST. One obvious option is to join an existing team
in your region. This can easily be done contacting your FIRST Regional Director. If there are no existing
teams near you there is always the option starting a new team yourself. This can be easily done and
the first suggested step is to contact your FIRST Regional Director. Going to regional/international
competitions and cheering on and interacting with the many teams that participate in the competition
is another viable form of involving oneself in FIRST. Spreading the message of FIRST through educating
youth on the joys of science and technology is another admirable form of getting involved with FIRST.

If you do not wish to join or start a team there is always the option of supporting local
teams. This can be done by donating to them. There is a page on the FIRST website that has all of
the information about donations. Volunteering your time to mentor students or helping out during
competitions are also encouraged. Another option is to become a team or event sponsor or supplier. If
you choose to do this you would be funding and/or supplying team(s) with needed supplies.</pre>